ZH: 这个灯泡已经坏了。
EN: This light bulb is already broken.

ZH: 请你帮我换一个新的灯泡。
EN: Can you help me replace a new light bulb?

ZH: 我买了一盒灯泡，以防万一。
EN: I bought a box of light bulbs, just in case.

ZH: 这个灯泡太亮了。
EN: This light bulb is too bright.

ZH: 他用手轻轻摸了一下灯泡。
EN: He touched the light bulb gently with his hand.

ZH: 这个灯泡有点小，可以吗？
EN: Is this light bulb a bit too small?

ZH: 我把灯泡拧下来了，但是它还是不亮。
EN: I unscrewed the light bulb, but it's still not working.

ZH: 弄坏了灯泡，我擦擦汗。
EN: I broke the light bulb and wiped off my sweat.

ZH: 请小心，灯泡很容易碎。
EN: Please be careful, light bulbs are very fragile.

ZH: 我的书桌上有一个漂亮的灯泡。
EN: There is a beautiful light bulb on my desk.

ZH: 客厅里的灯泡需要清洗。
EN: The light bulb in the living room needs to be cleaned.

ZH: 我昨天没注意，把灯泡打碎了。
EN: I accidentally broke the light bulb yesterday as I wasn't paying attention.

ZH: 请不要让孩子碰灯泡。
EN: Please do not let children touch the light bulb.

ZH: 来一个电工，我们的灯泡坏了。
EN: Call an electrician, our light bulb is broken.

ZH: 我的床头灯泡坏了，晚上睡觉没光。
EN: The light bulb in my bedside lamp is broken, so I can't see at night.

ZH: 不用点灯，我家的灯泡都换成了节能的。
EN: We don't need to turn on the lights, all the light bulbs in my house are energy-efficient.

ZH: 别担心，我会帮你买新的灯泡。
EN: Don't worry, I'll help you buy new light bulbs.

ZH: 客厅的灯泡太耗电了，我们应该换成LED灯。
EN: The light bulb in the living room consumes too much electricity, we should switch to LED lights.

ZH: 我在逛超市的时候，顺便买了几盏漂亮的灯泡。
EN: I bought some beautiful light bulbs when I was shopping at the supermarket.

ZH: 请打开灯泡，我找东西。
EN: Can you turn on the light bulb, I'm looking for something.
